        "INDIAN market suggestion": "To optimize AI Soil Health Monitoring for the Indian market, implement the following modifications:  - Integration with the Soil Health Card (SHC) Scheme: Align AI outputs with the Indian government\u2019s SHC initiative by digitizing existing physical card data and providing localized fertilizer dosage recommendations based on specific regional soil nutrient statuses.\n  - Offline-First and Low-Bandwidth Functionality: Design the system to operate via a WhatsApp-based interface where farmers can upload smartphone photos of soil or crops for instant diagnostics, reducing the need for high-bandwidth apps or expensive IoT sensors.\n  - Fractional and Shared Resource Models: Enable \"pay-per-scan\" or shared-access models for cooperatives and joint families, as Indian landholdings are often small and managed as multi-generational family enterprises where cost-sharing is common.\n  - Focus on Soil Organic Matter (SOM) and Salinity: Prioritize the detection of declining organic matter and salinity, which are critical issues in Indian soil health due to erratic monsoons and over-irrigation.\n  - Localized Weather Correlation: Use open-source AI weather models that don't require supercomputers to correlate soil health trends with local monsoon patterns, providing a 30-day advance advisory via SMS.",
