        "INDIAN market suggestion": "Based on current Indian AgTech trends and research, here are specific modifications to optimize AI Crop Disease Detection for the Indian market:  - Technical Adaptation: Use lightweight Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (D-CNN) like MobileNet or InceptionV3 optimized for low-end smartphones, as India has over 1 billion smartphone users but varying hardware quality.\n  - Strategic Focus: Prioritize detection for high-impact Indian crops such as Paddy (Blast), Wheat (Rust), Cotton (Boll Rot), and Tomato (Early Blight), which account for significant yield failures.\n  - Delivery Channel: Implement a WhatsApp-based chatbot for image uploads, as seen with startups like Kisan AI, to bypass App Store friction and high data usage for rural farmers.\n  - Frugal Hardware: Explore \"butterfly-shaped\" low-altitude flying robots or repurposed second-hand smartphones as field sensors to capture underside leaf images that overhead drones often miss.\n  - Sustainable Features: Integrate organic treatment suggestions and real-time weather API data to help farmers move away from expensive, blanket pesticide applications toward precision spraying.\n  - Government Alignment: Integrate with the Digital Agriculture Mission 2021-2025 or local Krishi Vigyan Kendras (KVKs) to build trust and leverage existing rural extension networks.",
