        "INDIAN market suggestion": "Based on current Indian aquaculture trends and research, here are specific modifications to optimize AI Aquaculture Management for the Indian market:  - Strategic Focus: Prioritize disease prediction and management for White Spot Syndrome Virus (WSSV) in shrimp, particularly in Andhra Pradesh which accounts for nearly 70% of India\u2019s production and faces 40% yield losses due to outbreaks.\n  - Delivery Channel: Implement a WhatsApp-based chatbot for feeding logs and water quality alerts to bypass rural connectivity issues and reduce dependency on high-cost technicians, following the success of platforms like FarmMOJO.\n  - Frugal Hardware: Support data entry from low-cost, locally manufactured IoT sensors (like those using Arduino or Raspberry Pi) to monitor critical Indian pond parameters like dissolved oxygen, pH, and ammonia without expensive imports.\n  - Financial Integration: Utilize AI-driven biomass and health data to provide \"credit-worthiness\" scores, helping smallholder farmers access formal loans and crop insurance through government schemes like PMMSY.\n  - Sustainable Features: Integrate biofloc-specific monitoring modules to help farmers reduce feed costs by up to 30% through improved nutrient recycling and waste management, which is a growing trend in land-based Indian aquaculture.\n  - Government Alignment: Align with the Pradhan Mantri Matsya Sampada Yojana (PMMSY) to leverage existing digital platforms like SISTA360 and build trust through local Krishi Vigyan Kendras (KVKs).",
