        "INDIAN market suggestion": "Based on current Indian maritime and environmental trends, here are specific modifications to optimize AI Oil Spill Detection for the Indian market:  - Technical Adaptation: Prioritize the fusion of Synthetic Aperture Radar (SAR) data from India's RISAT series with European Sentinel-1 data to ensure high-revisit monitoring of the Indian Exclusive Economic Zone (EEZ), especially during the cloud-heavy monsoon season.\n  - Strategic Focus: Focus monitoring on high-traffic energy corridors such as the Gulf of Kachchh (Gujarat) and the Mumbai High offshore fields, which handle a vast majority of India's crude oil imports and production.\n  - Delivery Channel: Develop a localized \"Coastal Alert\" WhatsApp interface for the Indian Coast Guard and State Maritime Boards to receive real-time coordinates and spill polygons, bypassing the need for complex desktop GIS software in the field.\n  - Frugal Hardware: Integrate with existing terrestrial maritime radar networks already installed along the Indian coastline under the National Radar Chain project to provide low-cost, near-shore verification without constant satellite tasking.\n  - Community Integration: Implement a crowdsourced validation feature for \"traditional\" fishing communities (Koli, Sangada, etc.) to report sightings via voice notes or photos, leveraging their 24/7 presence at sea to ground-truth AI detections.\n  - Government Alignment: Align outputs with the National Oil Spill Disaster Contingency Plan (NOS-DCP) to provide standardized reporting formats required by the Indian Coast Guard for official response activation.",
