        "INDIAN market suggestion": "Based on current Indian industrial safety trends and regulatory frameworks, here are specific modifications to optimize AI Hazardous Material Tracking for the Indian market:  - CPCB Compliance Integration: Align AI models to automatically flag violations based on the Central Pollution Control Board (CPCB) Hazardous and Other Wastes Rules 2016, specifically for chemical sludge and pharmaceutical byproducts.\n  - Multilingual Voice-Guided SOPs: Implement voice-based step-by-step guidance in Hindi, Marathi, and Gujarati to assist floor-level workers in hazardous zones who may have varying literacy levels or English proficiency.\n  - WhatsApp-Based Incident Reporting: Use a WhatsApp chatbot interface for real-time photo uploads and hazard flagging to bypass the need for complex enterprise apps in environments with intermittent connectivity.\n  - Low-Cost Edge Vision: Optimize computer vision models for affordable, locally available CCTV hardware and repurposed smartphones to detect PPE violations (like lack of safety gloves or masks) without requiring expensive high-end sensors.\n  - Logistics Geofencing: Integrate with the ULIP (Unified Logistics Interface Platform) and use GPS geofencing to ensure hazardous transport vehicles adhere to approved routes, avoiding high-density urban areas as per local municipal regulations.\n  - Emergency Response Automation: Connect the tracking system to automated SMS/call alerts for local fire departments and emergency response teams (ERT) to reduce reaction time during leaks or spills in industrial clusters like GIDC or MIDC.",
