        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for the vast industrial and manufacturing belts across Northern and Central India.\n  - Marathi: Critical for the major automotive and engineering clusters in Maharashtra, specifically the Pune-Nashik industrial corridor.\n  - Tamil: Vital for reaching the highly organized manufacturing and electronics hubs in South India.Critical surfaces to localize  - Real-time Alerts: Voice and text notifications for safety breaches must be understood instantly by floor workers.\n  - Training Modules: Safety protocols and compliance instructions must be localized to ensure effective knowledge transfer.\n  - Reporting Interface: Input fields for workers to log hazards or near-misses using local language or voice-to-text.\n  - Onboarding: Initial setup and app walkthroughs for supervisors and factory floor employees.Biggest localization risks  - Operational Safety: Misinterpretation of an English-only safety warning can lead to immediate physical injury or equipment damage.\n  - Low Worker Compliance: Employees may ignore or bypass safety checks if the interface feels complex or linguistically alien.\n  - Legal Liability: Indian labor laws and safety regulations often necessitate that instructions be provided in a language understood by the workforce.3-month pilot plan  - Translate core safety alert notifications into Hindi and Marathi for the initial deployment phase\n  - Implement a voice-first hazard reporting feature that supports regional dialects to accommodate varying literacy levels\n  - Roll out localized digital safety checklists for daily inspections at two pilot manufacturing sites\n  - Establish a feedback loop with safety officers to refine technical safety terminology in regional scripts",
