        "INDIAN market suggestion": "Based on current Indian occupational health and safety trends and research, here are specific modifications to optimize AI Ergonomics Assessment for the Indian market:  - Legal Alignment: Integrate compliance mapping for the Occupational Safety, Health and Working Conditions (OSH) Code 2020, specifically assisting with the mandatory annual health check-ups and safety committee requirements for factories with 500+ workers.\n  - Technical Adaptation: Optimize computer vision models for diverse Indian workplace environments, including varying lighting conditions in MSME units and non-standardized office furniture often found in smaller regional branches.\n  - Delivery Channel: Utilize a WhatsApp-based interface for video uploads and report delivery, bypassing the need for high-end hardware and making the tool accessible to field-level safety officers in tier-2 and tier-3 cities.\n  - Strategic Focus: Prioritize high-risk posture detection for sectors dominant in India, such as textile manufacturing, manual material handling in logistics, and prolonged sitting in the massive IT/BPO sector.\n  - Language & Accessibility: Provide localized voice-guided instructions and reports in Hindi, Kannada, and Telugu to ensure ground-level supervisors and workers can understand and implement corrective actions without English proficiency.\n  - Frugal Implementation: Offer a \"sensor-less\" smartphone-only mode that requires no specialized wearable gear, catering to the budget constraints of Indian SMEs while delivering automated RULA/REBA scores.\n  - Cultural Sensitivity: Include training modules for \"Healthy Desk Habits\" tailored to Indian hybrid work cultures, addressing specific local issues like screen glare from unshaded windows and non-adjustable seating.",
