        "family structure fit": "- Fit with joint families: High. In India, small and medium enterprises (SMEs) and home-based businesses are often multi-generational, where workspace and health responsibilities are shared across the household.\n  - Key conflicts: Younger generations may insist on tech-driven ergonomic changes (like expensive chairs or desk setups) that elders view as unnecessary \"lifestyle\" expenses; tension over sharing camera-enabled devices for assessment due to privacy concerns in shared living spaces.\n  - Joint-family-friendly features: Household-wide dashboard to track the posture health of all family members; \"Elder Mode\" with simplified UI and voice instructions for older family members managing the family business.\n  - Single best India family tweak: A \"Multi-User Home Office\" mode that optimizes a single shared workspace for different family members' body types (e.g., father, mother, and adult son) throughout the day, providing personalized setup alerts via a shared family WhatsApp group.",
