        "INDIAN market suggestion": "Based on current Indian HR Tech trends and digital infrastructure, here are specific modifications to optimize AI Background Screening for the Indian market:  - Digital Identity Integration: Seamlessly integrate with the India Stack, specifically using Aadhaar-based e-KYC and DigiLocker APIs to pull authenticated identity and education records instantly, bypassing manual document collection.\n  - UAN & PF Verification: Implement automated employment history validation through the Universal Account Number (UAN) and Employees' Provident Fund (EPF) database to detect \"moonlighting\" or undisclosed concurrent employment, a rising concern in the Indian IT sector.\n  - e-Court & Police Record Automation: Utilize the Indian e-Courts integrated mission mode project to scan district and high court records in real-time, reducing criminal verification turnaround from weeks to 3-5 days.\n  - Deepfake & Liveness Detection: Incorporate AI-driven facial recognition with liveness checks during the onboarding process to prevent \"proxy interviews\" and identity fraud, which have become prevalent in remote hiring for GCCs and tech firms.\n  - Multilingual OCR: Deploy Optical Character Recognition (OCR) models trained on regional Indian languages and varied document formats from Tier II/III city universities and local government bodies to ensure high accuracy in data extraction.\n  - Gig Workforce Scalability: Design lightweight, WhatsApp-integrated verification flows for high-volume blue-collar and gig economy hiring (e.g., delivery partners), allowing for 1-5 minute rapid background checks.\n  - Compliance with DPDP Act: Ensure the platform architecture is natively compliant with the Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act 2023, featuring granular consent management and data localization specifically for Indian citizen data.",
