        "INDIAN market suggestion": "Based on current Indian HR trends and recent legal developments, here are specific modifications to optimize AI Harassment Detection for the Indian market:  - Legal Framework Alignment: Integrate specific detection parameters for violations under the Sexual Harassment of Women at Workplace (Prevention, Prohibition and Redressal) Act, 2013 (POSH Act) and the Bharatiya Nyaya Sanhita (BNS) 2023, particularly sections regarding digital consent and \"nudifying\" AI.\n  - Multilingual & Code-Mixed NLP: Implement Natural Language Processing models capable of detecting harassment in English, Hindi, and \"Hinglish\" (code-mixed), as BERT-based models have shown high accuracy (93.5%) in identifying abusive Indian cultural nuances and slang.\n  - Deepfake & Image Authentication: Prioritize the detection of non-consensual AI-generated deepfakes and manipulated media, which are a rising threat to Indian women in professional spaces, using watermarking and content authentication standards.\n  - Delivery via Common Platforms: Build integration for WhatsApp and LinkedIn, the primary professional and semi-professional communication channels in India, to monitor and flag inappropriate language or predatory behavior in real-time.\n  - Interactive POSH Training: Use the AI core to generate immersive, scenario-based training programs that replace dry, text-heavy policies, helping employees recognize subtle forms of digital and verbal harassment specific to the Indian workplace.\n  - Support Ecosystem Integration: Link the detection system to automated grievance registration bots (similar to Haptik/AAH) that provide victims with immediate tips, mental health contacts, and direct links to local cyber cells or Internal Committees (IC).",
        "Kill Condition": "No PMF signals by Week 12",
