        "INDIAN market suggestion": "Based on current Indian governance trends and SEBI regulations, here are specific modifications to optimize AI Proxy Voting for the Indian market:  - Regulatory Integration: Align the AI model with SEBI's Stewardship Code and the \"Registrations and Grievance Redressal\" framework, ensuring all automated recommendations include the mandatory disclosures and rationales required for Indian Domestic Institutional Investors (DIIs).\n  - Strategic Focus: Prioritize analysis for common Indian corporate governance flashpoints, such as Related Party Transactions (RPTs), promoter remuneration, and board appointments in family-owned listed companies, which often face high scrutiny from domestic proxy firms like IiAS.\n  - Delivery Channel: Implement a WhatsApp-integrated notification system for retail investors to receive \"One-Tap Voting\" alerts and simplified summaries of resolutions, bypassing the low engagement rates typically seen in traditional email-based proxy communications in India.\n  - Language Localization: Offer summaries of shareholder resolutions and voting recommendations in major regional languages (e.g., Hindi, Marathi, Gujarati) to cater to the surging demographic of retail investors from Tier 2 and Tier 3 cities.\n  - Market Intelligence: Integrate a tracking module for \"Postal Ballots\" and \"Electronic Voting\" windows specific to the Indian market, providing real-time alerts for the 4-6 week pre-AGM engagement period recommended for Indian Investor Relations professionals.\n  - Compliance Automation: Automate the extraction of data from key Indian regulatory filings, such as the Business Responsibility and Sustainability Report (BRSR), to provide ESG-linked voting insights tailored to Indian sustainability standards.",
