        "INDIAN market suggestion": "Based on current Indian financial reporting trends and regulatory initiatives like the IndiaAI Innovation Challenge 2026, here are specific modifications to optimize AI Annual Report Generation for the Indian market:  - Regulatory Alignment: Integrate with the National Financial Reporting Authority (NFRA) standards and SEBI\u2019s Business Responsibility and Sustainability Reporting (BRSR) framework to ensure automated compliance with India-specific disclosure mandates.\n  - MSME Adaptation: Develop lightweight, cost-effective modules tailored for India's 7.5 crore MSMEs, focusing on shopfloor efficiency data and compliance automation to help them integrate into global supply chains.\n  - Delivery and Engagement: Implement a WhatsApp-based interface for data collection and report distribution, utilizing vernacular Small Language Models (SLMs) to support regional languages for stakeholders in diverse industrial clusters.\n  - Digital Infrastructure Linkage: Connect the AI model to India's Digital Public Infrastructure (DPI) and the Ministry of Corporate Affairs (MCA21) portal to streamline real-time filing and validation of financial statements.\n  - Audit and Trust: Incorporate the \"Responsible AI 2.0\" framework and RBI\u2019s FREE-AI guidelines to provide verifiable assurance, helping Indian enterprises overcome data governance and security skepticism.\n  - Sector-Specific Templates: Prioritize automated report generation for high-adoption sectors like BFSI and manufacturing, including specialized modules for ESG tracking and CSR impact reporting.",
