        "INDIAN market suggestion": "Based on current Indian ESG trends and regulatory requirements, here are specific modifications to optimize AI Sustainability Reporting for the Indian market:  - Regulatory Alignment: Prioritize automated data mapping for the Business Responsibility and Sustainability Reporting (BRSR) framework, which SEBI mandates for the top 1,000 listed companies in India.\n  - Strategic Focus: Incorporate specialized modules for \"Social\" metrics relevant to the Indian context, such as Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) spend tracking under the Companies Act and gender diversity ratios within the local workforce.\n  - Supply Chain Integration: Develop lightweight, mobile-first data collection tools for MSME suppliers to capture Scope 3 emissions data, addressing the common lack of digital infrastructure in Indian upstream value chains.\n  - Environmental Specifics: Integrate tracking for India-specific environmental challenges, particularly water stress levels and groundwater usage, which are high-priority disclosures for Indian industrial units.\n  - Language and Accessibility: Provide multi-lingual support (Hindi, Marathi, Tamil, etc.) for field-level data entry to ensure accuracy when gathering primary environmental and social data from rural factory or project sites.\n  - Audit Readiness: Build a \"pre-validation\" engine that flags inconsistencies against SEBI's 140-question BRSR format to reduce the time and cost of third-party assurance, which is increasingly required for Indian corporate filings.",
