        "INDIAN market suggestion": "Based on Indian HR trends and the 2026 labor market outlook, here are specific modifications to optimize AI Pay Transparency for the Indian market:  - Regulatory Compliance: Automate the tracking and maintenance of mandatory wage registers (Forms A-E) under the Code on Wages 2019 to ensure organizations are \"inspection-ready\" for government labor officials.\n  - Skills-Based Benchmarking: Prioritize skill-based pay mapping over traditional job titles to account for the 40% pay premiums currently seen in India\u2019s emerging tech and specialized roles.\n  - Tiered Geographical Data: Incorporate hyper-local benchmarking that distinguishes between Tier 1, 2, and 3 cities to address the widening pay gaps and varying receptivity to transparency across different Indian regions.\n  - Mobile-First Delivery: Use WhatsApp-integrated interfaces for employee self-service to allow workers to query pay ranges and equity status, aligning with India's high mobile-first workforce engagement.\n  - Performance-Linkage: Integrate variable pay and bonus transparency modules to reflect the shift in Indian corporate strategy from uniform increments to high-differentiation, performance-linked rewards.",
