        "INDIAN market suggestion": "Based on current Indian HR tech trends and research, here are specific modifications to optimize AI Benefits Communication for the Indian market:  - Technical Adaptation: Integrate with WhatsApp and MS Teams for delivery, as these are the primary communication hubs for Indian white-collar and blue-collar workers, ensuring higher open rates than email.\n  - Strategic Focus: Prioritize clear communication for high-demand Indian benefits including Employee State Insurance (ESI), Provident Fund (EPF) updates, and specialized family healthcare covers that include parents and in-laws.\n  - Delivery Channel: Use AI-powered multilingual voice-bots and chatbots to explain complex tax-saving components like HRA, LTA, and Section 80C investments in regional languages for a diverse workforce.\n  - Frugal Hardware: Optimize for mobile-first consumption, ensuring the AI interface remains lightweight for low-bandwidth areas where remote or field employees may be located.\n  - Sustainable Features: Automate the generation of personalized \"Total Rewards\" statements that visually break down the Indian CTC (Cost to Company) structure to help employees appreciate the non-cash value of their benefits.\n  - Government Alignment: Ensure the AI model stays updated with evolving Indian labor laws, the New Wage Code, and EPFO circulars to provide real-time, compliant answers to employee queries.",
