        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for the massive freelancer pools and SME business users in North and Central India (Delhi-NCR, Jaipur, Indore).\n  - Kannada: Critical for the technology and startup hub of Bengaluru, where a significant portion of the tech-enabled gig workforce is located.\n  - Tamil: Vital for the industrial and software services ecosystem in Chennai and Coimbatore, connecting local businesses with regional talent.Critical surfaces to localize  - UX and Navigation: Dashboard and filtering systems to allow business users to easily toggle between language preferences.\n  - Support and Onboarding: Localized chatbots and help documentation to guide SMEs through the process of posting jobs and vetting freelancers.\n  - Marketing: Ad campaigns and landing pages tailored to regional business pain points and success stories from local \"Bharat\" entrepreneurs.\n  - Legal: Summarized versions of freelancer agreements and terms of service in local scripts to ensure trust and transparency.Biggest localization risks  - Trust Deficit: A \"Western-only\" English interface may alienate traditional SME owners who prefer conducting business in their native tongue or Hinglish.\n  - Search Inaccuracy: If skills and job descriptions aren't mapped to local terminology (e.g., \"Mistry\" for certain skilled trades), matching quality will drop for non-tech roles.\n  - Payment Friction: Confusion over localized invoicing and tax terms (GST) if presented only in complex English legal jargon.3-month pilot plan  - Build a bilingual MVP (English and Hindi) focusing on the core job-matching algorithm\n  - Localize the freelancer profile creation flow for Kannada to target the Bengaluru tech-gig market\n  - Implement a WhatsApp-based notification system in 3 languages for real-time match alerts\n  - Partner with one regional industry association to validate the clarity of localized support materials\n  - Create a localized \"How to Hire\" video guide in Hindi for first-time business users",
