        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for communication with municipal authorities and ground staff across the North Indian transport belt.\n  - Marathi: Critical for the high-density traffic and logistics hubs in Mumbai and Pune.\n  - Kannada: Vital for integration with the tech-heavy traffic management systems in Bengaluru.Critical surfaces to localize  - UX and Dashboard: Real-time alerts and traffic status labels for control room operators.\n  - Support and Onboarding: Technical documentation and training manuals for government field staff.\n  - Legal: Compliance documents and service level agreements (SLAs) with state-level transport departments.\n  - Marketing: Case studies and pitch decks for state government tenders and smart city initiatives.Biggest localization risks  - Technical Jargon: Standardized transport engineering terms may lack precise translations, leading to operational errors.\n  - Regional Policy Nuances: Traffic laws and reporting formats vary by state, making a \"one-size-fits-all\" translation ineffective.\n  - Inter-agency Friction: Communication gaps between English-speaking tech teams and regional-language government officials can delay deployments.3-month pilot plan  - Develop a bilingual (English/Hindi) interface for the primary traffic monitoring dashboard\n  - Translate the 3-page \"Field Operator Guide\" into Hindi and Marathi for pilot site staff\n  - Create a localized WhatsApp-based alert system for critical traffic incident notifications\n  - Establish a weekly feedback session with local operators to refine technical terminology in the local script",
