        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for national-level policy alignment and large transit networks across North and Central India.\n  - Marathi: Critical for Mumbai and Pune, which represent India's most complex and high-volume public transit systems.\n  - Kannada: Necessary for Bengaluru (BMTC), a primary hub for tech-first transit innovation and pilot programs.Critical surfaces to localize  - Operator Dashboards: Ground staff and drivers require real-time optimization alerts in their primary language.\n  - Training & Onboarding: Technical instruction modules and tutorial videos for fleet managers and field staff.\n  - Commuter Feedback Portals: Localized interfaces to ensure accurate reporting and data collection from the public.\n  - Compliance & Reporting: Simplified regulatory summaries for local municipal authorities and government officials.Biggest localization risks  - Operational Misalignment: Critical real-time adjustments may be ignored or misunderstood by ground staff if provided only in English.\n  - Data Quality Gaps: Public feedback and sentiment analysis will be skewed or incomplete without support for regional languages.\n  - Institutional Resistance: Adoption may be hindered by local unions or administrative bodies who perceive English-only tools as inaccessible.3-month pilot plan  - Launch a bilingual (English and Hindi) management interface with togglable language settings.\n  - Deploy a localized mobile dashboard for a small group of ground operators in one regional hub.\n  - Develop visual training guides with translated captions for rapid onboarding of transit staff.\n  - Establish a WhatsApp-based support channel for operators using regional voice-to-text features.",
