        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for broad accessibility among strategy teams and leadership in Northern India's industrial and corporate hubs.\n  - Kannada: Critical for the high-density tech and startup ecosystem in Bengaluru, where many strategic \"war rooms\" are based.\n  - Marathi: Necessary to engage the financial and corporate headquarters in Mumbai and the manufacturing corridors of Pune.Critical surfaces to localize  - UX and Navigation: Dashboard labels and simulation controls to ensure intuitive use during high-pressure strategy sessions.\n  - Content and Scenarios: Localized market data, competitor profiles, and regulatory context (e.g., SEBI, RBI norms) within the war game modules.\n  - Onboarding and Support: Training manuals and video walkthroughs to reduce the learning curve for senior executives.\n  - Legal and Compliance: Data privacy terms and non-disclosure agreements aligned with the Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act.Biggest localization risks  - Nuance in Strategy: Strategic terminology often lacks direct translations, leading to misinterpretation of simulation outcomes or advice.\n  - Regional Market Context: Failure to capture local business nuances (e.g., promoter-led dynamics) in the AI model can result in irrelevant strategy recommendations.\n  - Trust in AI: English-only platforms may be perceived as \"western-centric,\" causing users to doubt the AI's understanding of Indian market complexities.3-month pilot plan  - Develop a bilingual (English/Hindi) MVP interface for the core simulation engine\n  - Localize 5-10 strategy \"scenarios\" specifically focusing on Indian market entry and competitor defense\n  - Create a WhatsApp-based support bot in Hindi and Kannada to assist users during the pilot phase\n  - Partner with 2 Indian corporate strategy teams to validate the accuracy of localized terminology and scenario relevance",
