        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for broad adoption across North Indian industrial hubs and logistics centers.\n  - Marathi: Critical for Mumbai and Pune's financial and industrial risk management sectors.\n  - Kannada: Vital for the high-concentration tech and risk-modeling talent in Bengaluru.Critical surfaces to localize  - Legal and Compliance: Data privacy notices and risk disclosure agreements to meet DPDP Act requirements.\n  - Onboarding: Instructional walkthroughs and \"How-it-works\" videos for diverse technical teams.\n  - Support: Multilingual help desk and WhatsApp-integrated incident reporting for real-time risk updates.\n  - Marketing: Localized case studies and whitepapers highlighting regional regulatory nuances.Biggest localization risks  - Technical Accuracy: Precision loss when translating complex risk modeling terminology into regional scripts.\n  - Trust Deficit: Security-focused products may be perceived as less \"official\" if localized poorly or inconsistently.\n  - Regulatory Complexity: Risk frameworks (like SEBI or RBI) use English as the primary language; mixing languages can lead to interpretative errors.3-month pilot plan  - Develop a core English interface with Hindi-localized support and legal documentation.\n  - Create a localized video series explaining the \"Digital Twin\" concept for non-English speaking stakeholders.\n  - Implement a Hinglish (Hindi-English) chatbot for rapid user onboarding and query resolution.\n  - Validate translation accuracy with a focus group of 5-10 risk professionals in Mumbai or Bengaluru.",
