        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for broad accessibility among risk officers and business owners across North and Central India's industrial hubs.\n  - Kannada: Critical for the technology and startup ecosystem in Bengaluru, where real-time monitoring is high-stakes.\n  - Marathi: Vital for the financial and manufacturing sectors in Mumbai and Pune to ensure local compliance and risk reporting.Critical surfaces to localize  - Alerts and Notifications: High-priority risk alerts must be delivered in local languages via WhatsApp or SMS to ensure immediate action.\n  - Dashboard Reporting: Risk summaries and categorization should be available in the user's preferred language for clarity during crises.\n  - Onboarding and Training: Step-by-step guides and risk-parameter setup modules to ensure non-technical users configure the AI correctly.\n  - Support and Legal: Crisis management protocols and localized compliance documentation aligned with Indian regulatory standards.Biggest localization risks  - Translation Accuracy: Misinterpretation of complex legal or financial risk terminology could lead to incorrect mitigation steps.\n  - Sentiment Nuance: AI models may struggle to detect regional linguistic nuances in local news or social media, missing early risk signals.\n  - Cultural Context: Risk thresholds vary by region; an English-only \"one size fits all\" approach may trigger excessive false positives or miss localized threats.3-month pilot plan  - Develop a bilingual (English/Hindi) MVP notification system for critical risk alerts\n  - Localize the onboarding workflow for 10-20 beta users in the Mumbai or Bengaluru regions\n  - Create a localized library of common Indian regulatory and operational risk categories\n  - Implement a feedback loop to refine technical translations of risk terminology with local industry experts",
