        "FESTIVAL INTEGRATION": "Top Relevant Festivals  - International Day of Yoga: National focus on physical wellness and mobility, providing a perfect entry point for AI-driven posture correction\n  - Diwali: A period of renewal and \"New Year\" resolutions where families invest in long-term health solutions for elders\n  - Rakhi: A festival of protection where siblings can gift \"Recovery and Mobility\" packages to one another\n  - Durga Puja: Involves extensive walking and standing, leading to a seasonal spike in demand for joint and muscle recovery\n  - World Senior Citizens Day: Highly relevant for marketing rehabilitation services as a gift for elderly parents in joint families\n  - Ganesh Chaturthi: Large community gatherings allow for on-ground posture screening camps and mass awareness\n  - Holi: Increased incidence of minor slips or muscle strains creates a short-term demand for immediate at-home recovery guidanceFestival-specific Opportunity Ideas  - Gift of Mobility: Launch a Rakhi and Diwali campaign allowing users to purchase rehabilitation subscriptions for their parents or grandparents\n  - Pandal-Hopping Recovery: Offer specialized AI-guided stretches and quick recovery modules during Durga Puja for people experiencing foot or back pain\n  - Yoga Day Posture Scan: Provide a free \"AI Posture Audit\" on International Day of Yoga to drive app downloads and identify potential rehab needs\n  - Resolution Discounts: Run \"New Health Year\" annual subscription bundles during Diwali to capture the seasonal spend on family wellness\n  - Community Wellness Kiosks: Set up digital screening stations at large Ganesh Chaturthi pandals to demonstrate the AI's ability to track movement\n  - Sports Day Injury Clinics: Partner with local sports clubs on National Sports Day to offer AI-led injury rehabilitation modules for amateur athletesHero Campaign Concept\n\"Dadi's Digital Steps\" (Grandmother's Digital Steps): A Diwali-focused campaign highlighting how the AI platform helps elders in the family regain mobility at home. The campaign features a \"Grandchild-to-Grandparent\" onboarding challenge, where the younger generation helps the elder set up their AI rehab plan, positioning the tech as a bridge for family care during the festive season.\n\nKey Risks and Mitigations  - Cultural Sensitivity: Rehabilitation exercises may conflict with religious fasting or prayer times; mitigate by offering \"Low-Energy\" routines and flexible scheduling alerts\n  - Support Load: Spikes in festive users can overwhelm customer service; mitigate by deploying a multilingual WhatsApp bot to handle common onboarding and setup queries\n  - Connectivity Issues: High network congestion during large festivals can lag real-time AI feedback; mitigate by allowing users to download exercise videos for offline use\n  - High Acquisition Costs: Ad spends skyrocket during Diwali; mitigate by focusing on community-led WhatsApp referrals and organic influencer partnerships within health niches",
        "JUGAAD": "- Top 3 current cost drivers: Specialized medical-grade motion sensors/wearables, high-cost cloud infrastructure for real-time 3D skeletal tracking, and expensive clinical data labeling by certified physiotherapists\n  - Description of a jugaad MVP: A WhatsApp-based bot where patients upload videos of their exercises recorded on budget smartphones; a lightweight computer vision model provides corrective feedback and counts repetitions, focusing on the 10 most common post-surgery movements\n  - User-side hacks/customizations possible: Using colored tape or household stickers as anatomical markers for better tracking, DIY phone stands made from water bottles or cardboard, and family members recording voice notes to annotate pain levels during specific movements\n  - Biggest 10x cost-down opportunity: Replacing proprietary hardware sensors and high-end LIDAR with smartphone-based 2D pose estimation and moving AI inference from expensive cloud servers to the user's local mobile device edge-processing"
