        "FESTIVAL INTEGRATION": "Top Relevant Festivals  - Diwali: Major corporate audit season where businesses refresh digital assets and seek \"prosperous\" inclusive growth\n  - Independence Day: National focus on \"Digital India\" and social equality, aligning with accessibility as a fundamental right\n  - International Day of Persons with Disabilities: The primary industry event in India to showcase commitment to inclusive tech\n  - Global Accessibility Awareness Day: Key timing for targeting the tech-forward developer communities in Bengaluru and Hyderabad\n  - Durga Puja: Peak e-commerce season where accessible UI is critical for capturing the widest possible consumer base\n  - Republic Day: Emphasis on constitutional rights and equal opportunity, providing a platform for \"Aatmanirbhar\" inclusive softwareFestival-specific Opportunity Ideas  - The Inclusive Sale: Partner with e-commerce platforms during Diwali to provide free accessibility audits for their festive landing pages\n  - Digital Equality Grants: Offer discounted AI-testing credits to Indian social impact startups during the week of Independence Day\n  - Accessibility Hackathons: Sponsor developer challenges during Global Accessibility Awareness Day to integrate the AI tool into local OSS projects\n  - State of the Nation Report: Release a benchmark study on the accessibility of top 100 Indian apps during Republic Day to drive B2B leads\n  - Inclusive Gifting: Allow corporate partners to \"gift\" an accessibility audit to one of their vendor's websites during the festive season\n  - Regional Outreach: Launch localized training modules in Hindi and Tamil during regional festivals like Pongal to reach diverse developer hubsHero Campaign Concept\n\"Bharat for All\": A month-long campaign leading up to International Day of Persons with Disabilities where the startup offers 100 free \"Accessibility Certificates\" to the first 100 Indian SMEs that pass an automated AI scan, promoted through LinkedIn and WhatsApp to Indian CTO circles.\n\nKey Risks and Mitigations  - High Support Load: Spike in audit requests during peak sale months; mitigate by leveraging fully automated AI reporting tiers that require zero human intervention\n  - Cultural Sensitivity: Risk of appearing to \"exploit\" social causes for sales; mitigate by co-creating campaign messaging with Indian disability advocacy groups\n  - Staff Availability: Regional holidays like Diwali or Puja reduce manual QA support; mitigate by ensuring the MVP is robustly automated for self-service onboarding\n  - Corporate Budget Freezes: Year-end spending might be locked; mitigate by offering \"Pre-Festive\" early bird pricing in September to secure Q4 contracts",
