        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for accessing the massive workforce and data labeling pools in North and Central India.\n  - Tamil: Critical for the mature IT and BPO clusters in Chennai and Coimbatore that handle high-volume data processing.\n  - Telugu: Necessary for tapping into the large talent pools in Hyderabad's tech and media-heavy annotation market.Critical surfaces to localize  - Onboarding and Training: Guidelines and task instructions must be clear to ensure data quality from non-English speakers.\n  - UX and Navigation: Dashboard labels and feedback tools for annotators to ensure high throughput.\n  - Support: Localized help desk and WhatsApp-based troubleshooting for workers.\n  - Legal: Consent forms and worker agreements in regional languages to ensure compliance with the DPDP Act 2023.Biggest localization risks  - Technical Jargon: Misinterpretation of complex annotation taxonomies if not translated with high precision.\n  - Context Loss: AI content nuances (like sarcasm or local idioms) failing if the annotator and the interface aren't linguistically aligned.\n  - Quality Inconsistency: High error rates in labeling if instructions are ambiguously translated into regional dialects.3-month pilot plan  - Translate core training modules and labeling guidelines into Hindi and Tamil\n  - Build a simplified, bilingual mobile-responsive interface for the initial batch of 50 annotators\n  - Implement a WhatsApp-based support bot in Hindi to handle real-time worker queries\n  - Conduct weekly quality audits on localized tasks to refine translation of technical instructions",
