        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for broad market penetration across Northern and Western India, where business operations and internal communications often blend English and Hindi (Hinglish).\n  - Kannada: Critical for the Bengaluru tech hub, ensuring the search tool is accessible to administrative and support staff in the primary startup ecosystem.\n  - Tamil: Vital for reaching the industrial and corporate sectors in Chennai and Coimbatore, where regional language pride and usage are high in business environments.Critical surfaces to localize  - UX and Navigation: Search bars and filter categories must support multilingual text input and display.\n  - Search Query Processing: The NLP engine must recognize Hinglish and regional language synonyms for business terms and document types.\n  - Support and Onboarding: Tooltips, help docs, and video tutorials for non-English dominant staff.\n  - Marketing: Case studies and sales decks for regional SMEs that prefer transacting in their primary language.Biggest localization risks  - Query Intent Misalignment: AI may fail to accurately map regional language queries to English-heavy document databases, leading to poor search relevance.\n  - Script Rendering Issues: Technical documents often contain complex formatting that may break when localized scripts are overlaid in the UI.\n  - Trust and Accuracy: Inaccurate translations of legal or financial search results can lead to business errors, causing users to revert to manual search.3-month pilot plan  - Implement a bilingual (English/Hindi) search interface for the core dashboard.\n  - Enable basic NLP support for \"Hinglish\" queries to handle mixed-language natural language searches.\n  - Localize the onboarding sequence and \"How-to\" guides for 10-20 beta users in Bengaluru and Mumbai.\n  - Establish a manual feedback tag for \"Incorrect Search Results\" to identify and fix regional language mapping errors.",
