        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for the broad enterprise and SME market across Northern and Central India.\n  - Tamil: Critical for the technologically mature and organized business sectors in South India.\n  - Kannada: Vital for targeting the high-density startup and tech-business hub of Bengaluru.Critical surfaces to localize  - Marketing: Landing pages and regional success stories to build trust with local business owners.\n  - Onboarding: Instructional tooltips and guided walkthroughs to reduce technical friction for non-native users.\n  - Content Generation: The core engine must support regional syntax and cultural context to produce relevant simulations.\n  - Support: Localized documentation and help center guides for troubleshooting.Biggest localization risks  - Cultural Disconnect: Simulations may feel inorganic or \"robotic\" if they do not account for regional idioms and business etiquette.\n  - Trust Deficit: English-only tools are often perceived as overly complex for daily operations in Tier 2 and Tier 3 cities.\n  - Input Limitations: The engine might fail to process code-switching (e.g., Hinglish) effectively without specific local training.3-month pilot plan  - Launch a bilingual (English and Hindi) MVP landing page and sign-up flow\n  - Localize the primary dashboard navigation and top 5 onboarding tooltips for Tamil users\n  - Partner with 10 regional business influencers to validate the cultural relevance of simulated outputs\n  - Implement a voice-to-text feedback mechanism in 3 languages to capture local dialect nuances for the simulation model",
