        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for reaching the massive base of content creators and businesses in Northern and Central India (Bharat).\n  - Bengali: Critical for the high-growth digital content and marketing hubs in West Bengal and the Eastern region.\n  - Tamil: Vital for the sophisticated tech and media ecosystem in South India, which has a strong preference for native-language interfaces.Critical surfaces to localize  - UX and Navigation: Menus, tooltips, and dashboard labels must be available in local scripts to reduce cognitive load for non-native English users.\n  - Content Output: The modeling engine must support Devanagari, Bengali, and Tamil scripts for generating relevant localized marketing and content models.\n  - Support and Onboarding: Localized video tutorials and WhatsApp-based support to guide users through complex technical setup and feature adoption.\n  - Legal: Terms of service and data privacy agreements should be translated to ensure clear understanding and compliance with the DPDP Act 2023.Biggest localization risks  - Script Rendering Issues: Improper handling of complex Indian scripts (ligatures and glyphs) in the UI can lead to unreadable text and a poor user experience.\n  - Nuance Loss: Standard translation tools often fail to capture the context-specific \"Hinglish\" or regional business terminology, making the tool feel generic and unhelpful.\n  - Adoption Friction: If the onboarding is English-only, the tool will likely see high churn among Tier 2 and Tier 3 business users who perceive it as too complex.3-month pilot plan  - Implement a high-quality Hindi translation for the primary dashboard and onboarding flow\n  - Support UTF-8 encoding for the core engine to enable content modeling in Hindi, Bengali, and Tamil\n  - Create localized \"Quick Start\" guides in Hindi and Tamil to distribute during the initial user validation phase\n  - Launch a dedicated WhatsApp support channel with automated responses in the three target languages",
