        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for reaching medical professionals and staff in Northern and Central Indian states where it is the primary medium of communication.\n  - Tamil: Critical for the robust private healthcare ecosystem in Tamil Nadu, which is a leading hub for specialized medical tourism and practice.\n  - Telugu: Vital for the extensive network of specialty hospitals and clinics in Andhra Pradesh and Telangana.Critical surfaces to localize  - UX and UI: Dashboards and navigation labels must support regional scripts for nursing and administrative staff.\n  - Clinical Documentation: The core AI engine must accurately transcribe and translate \"Hinglish\" and regional medical colloquialisms into formal English clinical notes.\n  - Onboarding and Training: Video tutorials and help documentation for doctors and medical scribes.\n  - Consent and Legal: Patient data privacy (DPDP) consent forms and terms of service must be available in the patient\u2019s primary language.Biggest localization risks  - Technical Accuracy: Incorrect translation of specialized medical terminology or symptoms could lead to clinical documentation errors and patient safety risks.\n  - Accents and Dialects: AI may struggle with diverse regional accents or the mixing of local languages with English (code-switching) during fast-paced consultations.\n  - Regulatory Compliance: Failure to provide legally binding consent forms in a language the patient understands may violate Indian medical ethics and data protection laws.3-month pilot plan  - Develop a bilingual (English/Hindi) interface for the note-generation dashboard.\n  - Fine-tune the speech-to-text model on 100+ hours of recorded specialty consultations featuring regional Indian accents.\n  - Implement localized patient consent modules in 3 languages to ensure compliance with the DPDP Act.\n  - Launch a pilot with 5 specialty clinics in a Hindi-speaking region and 5 in a Tamil-speaking region to compare transcription performance and user adoption.",
