        "FESTIVAL INTEGRATION": "Top Relevant Festivals  - Diwali: Major period for business planning and new tech investments for Indian SMEs and startups\n  - Engineers' Day: Significant celebration in Indian tech hubs to honor the engineering community\n  - Durga Puja: Large-scale hiring and project completion rush in East India before the long break\n  - Holi: Peak season for \"Spring Cleaning\" of old tech debt and preparation for the new fiscal year\n  - Ganesha Chaturthi: Auspicious time for Mumbai and Pune-based tech companies to launch new products/infrastructure\n  - Rakhi: Opportunity for \"Protect your Code\" marketing, playing on the theme of sibling protection and securityFestival-specific Opportunity Ideas  - \"Muhurat Documentation\": Launch special automated doc-generation bundles during Diwali to help teams start the new business year with clean codebases\n  - Engineering Excellence Awards: Run a social media campaign on Engineers' Day rewarding the \"Best Documented Repo\" to drive user engagement and platform sign-ups\n  - Pre-Pujo Sprint Cleanup: Offer intensive onboarding support or temporary \"unlimited repository\" scans in September to help teams document code before the Durga Puja holidays\n  - \"New Year, No Debt\" Campaign: Use the April New Year period (Gudi Padwa/Ugadi) to target CTOs wanting to eliminate \"documentation debt\" as part of their annual budget\n  - Founders' Protection Pack: Introduce a referral program during Rakhi where developers can \"gift\" documentation health checks to their colleagues' startup repos\n  - Offline Workshops: Host \"Clean Code\" seminars at local tech meetups during Bangalore\u2019s various cultural festivals to build a developer community presenceHero Campaign Concept\n\"Diwali Documentation Deep-Clean\": A 2-week campaign leading up to Diwali where the AI tool offers a free \"Code Health Report Card\" for any public repo. The campaign uses the traditional Indian concept of cleaning one's home before the festival, positioning outdated code comments and missing docs as \"clutter\" that hinders prosperity. Teams that achieve 90%+ documentation completeness during the window get featured on a \"Wall of Fame\" and receive limited-edition \"Clean Code\" swag.\n\nKey Risks and Mitigations  - Low Developer Activity: Reduced commits and activity during major festivals like Diwali; mitigate by running the campaign in the 3 weeks leading up to the holiday rather than the holiday week itself\n  - Support Availability: High demand for onboarding just before breaks; mitigate by deploying an automated AI assistant for technical setup issues and ensuring staggered shifts for the customer success team\n  - Market Noise: High ad costs and competition for attention during festive sales; mitigate by focusing on organic LinkedIn/Twitter developer communities and GitHub-specific outreach rather than broad social media ads\n  - Cultural Sensitivity: Ensuring the \"Clean Code\" metaphor is used respectfully; mitigate by focusing on the positive outcome of \"clarity and growth\" rather than purely on the \"mess\" of the existing codebase",
