        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages (max 3)  - Hindi: Necessary for the vast workforce in North and Central India and for blue-collar/entry-level employees.\n  - Bengali: Critical for reaching the massive talent pool and industrial hubs in West Bengal and neighboring regions.\n  - Tamil: Essential for the highly industrialized and tech-heavy employment market in Tamil Nadu.Critical surfaces to localize  - UX and Navigation: Language toggles and intuitive iconography for users who may find English financial terminology intimidating.\n  - Content and Explanations: Definitions of \"pay parity,\" \"compensation components,\" and \"market benchmarks\" using local business idioms.\n  - Onboarding and Privacy: Clear, localized explanations of data security and the Digital Personal Data Protection (DPDP) Act to build trust with employees sharing sensitive salary data.\n  - Support and FAQ: Chatbots or help centers available in local languages to handle complex queries regarding salary disputes or calculations.Biggest localization risks  - Legal Accuracy: Misinterpreting legal definitions from the Code on Wages 2019 during translation could lead to compliance errors or employee misinformation.\n  - Cultural Nuance: Discussions around salary are often culturally sensitive; a tone that is too aggressive or too vague in local languages may alienate users.\n  - Technical Jargon: Financial terms like \"variable pay\" or \"ESOPs\" may not have direct equivalents, requiring descriptive translations that risk being wordy and cluttering the UI.3-month pilot plan  - Develop a trilingual interface (English, Hindi, and Tamil) focusing on the core \"Salary Comparison\" feature.\n  - Localize all consent forms and privacy notices to ensure compliance with the DPDP Act 2023 for the pilot group.\n  - Partner with one North Indian and one South Indian firm to test the clarity of localized \"Pay Equity Reports\" with their employees.\n  - Implement a WhatsApp-based localized feedback loop to identify and fix confusing translations in real-time.",
