        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages (max 3)  - Hindi: Crucial for semi-urban and rural business owners who represent the fastest-growing segment of the Indian economy.\n  - Tamil: Essential for targeting the highly organized industrial and manufacturing hubs in South India.\n  - Bengali: Key for capturing the large MSME and creative professional market in the eastern region.Critical surfaces to localize  - UX and Navigation: Simple, icon-driven interface with regional language labels for high-frequency actions.\n  - Legal and Compliance: Localized drafting of contracts and legal documents to ensure alignment with Indian jurisdictional terminology and the DPDP Act 2023.\n  - Onboarding and Support: WhatsApp-based voice-guided onboarding and support documentation in the user's primary language.\n  - Marketing: Localized case studies and pricing pages (INR-specific) to build trust and demonstrate local relevance.Biggest localization risks  - Legal Accuracy: Precise translation of legal jargon is difficult; incorrect terminology can lead to unenforceable contracts or regulatory non-compliance.\n  - Dialect Nuance: Regional variations (e.g., UP vs. Bihar Hindi) may lead to friction in \"Hinglish\" voice-to-text features.\n  - Trust Deficit: A lack of native-language support in financial or legal products often leads users to stick with traditional, offline manual processes.3-month pilot plan  - Develop a bilingual (English/Hindi) MVP focusing on 5 core legal/business templates\n  - Integrate a WhatsApp-based multilingual notification system for status updates\n  - Partner with 5 local trade associations to test localized UI with non-English speaking founders\n  - Implement a regional language feedback loop to refine legal terminology based on local practice",
