        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for trust and mass adoption among kirana owners and small manufacturers across the Northern and Central Indian \"Bharat\" market.\n  - Marathi: Critical for the high density of small-scale manufacturing units and SMEs in the industrial hubs of Maharashtra.\n  - Tamil: Vital for the organized SME and textile manufacturing clusters in Tamil Nadu, where regional language preference is exceptionally high.Critical surfaces to localize  - Voice Interface: All voice-to-text commands for bookkeeping and inventory must support regional phonetics.\n  - WhatsApp Chatbot: Automated responses and marketing templates must use colloquial regional scripts.\n  - Onboarding: Tutorial videos and first-time setup guides should be dubbed or subtitled in local languages.\n  - Support: Customer helpdesk and FAQ sections to resolve technical queries in the user's native tongue.Biggest localization risks  - Technical Accuracy: Financial terms like \"inventory\" or \"ledger\" may not have direct equivalents in spoken dialects, requiring the use of common loanwords (Hinglish/local slang).\n  - High Churn: If the voice AI fails to recognize heavy regional accents or code-switching, users will revert to manual paper-based methods.\n  - Perceived Complexity: English interfaces often intimidate non-tech-savvy SME owners, leading to a lack of \"digital confidence\" and abandonment.3-month pilot plan  - Launch a bilingual (English/Hindi) WhatsApp MVP to test core bookkeeping features\n  - Implement a voice-first data entry module supporting Hindi and Marathi for 50 test users\n  - Localize all marketing collateral and WhatsApp broadcast templates into 3 languages\n  - Establish a manual regional-language support line to capture and document linguistic edge cases for AI training",
