        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for accessing the vast student and teacher population across the \"Hindi Belt\" in North and Central India.\n  - Bengali: Critical for reaching the massive, education-focused student demographic in West Bengal, one of India's largest regional markets.\n  - Telugu: Vital for the high-competition exam hubs in Andhra Pradesh and Telangana where local language support is a major differentiator.Critical surfaces to localize  - UX and Navigation: Simple, intuitive interface with regional language menus to ensure students from non-English backgrounds can navigate independently.\n  - Content and Curriculum: Translation of textbook concepts, practice questions, and exam-specific terminology to align with state board standards.\n  - Onboarding and Support: WhatsApp-integrated chatbots and tutorial videos in local languages to assist with initial setup and troubleshooting.\n  - Legal and Privacy: Clear, localized summaries of data usage under the DPDP Act 2023 to build trust with parents and schools.Biggest localization risks  - Technical Nuance: Scientific and mathematical terms may not have easy-to-understand translations, potentially causing confusion if not mapped correctly to the curriculum.\n  - Regional Dialects: Variations in \"Hinglish\" or regional accents can cause AI speech recognition or search features to fail if only standardized versions are used.\n  - Trust Deficit: English-only platforms are often perceived as elitist or \"extra-curricular,\" leading to lower adoption in government and budget private schools.3-month pilot plan  - Launch a bilingual (English/Hindi) MVP focusing on one core subject like Mathematics or Science\n  - Create a library of localized video guides and WhatsApp-based onboarding instructions in the 3 target languages\n  - Partner with 2-3 regional schools to test the effectiveness of AI-generated study summaries in local scripts\n  - Implement a voice-first feedback mechanism to capture and iterate on regional accent variations for the AI model",
