        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages (max 3)  - Hindi: Essential for ensuring wide adoption among board members and promoters in the Northern and Central Indian corporate hubs.\n  - Marathi: Critical for the high concentration of listed companies and financial institutions headquartered in Mumbai and Pune.\n  - Kannada: Vital for technology-driven startups and corporate boards based in the Bengaluru ecosystem.Critical surfaces to localize  - Legal and Regulatory: Compliance dashboards must accurately translate complex SEBI and MCA regulations into local legal terminology.\n  - UX and Navigation: Board portals and voting interfaces should provide local language toggles for ease of use during high-stakes meetings.\n  - Training and Onboarding: Educational modules for directors on fiduciary duties and new AI regulations need regional context.\n  - Support: Multilingual help desks to assist directors who may prefer discussing sensitive governance issues in their native language.Biggest localization risks  - Legal Accuracy: Misinterpretation of nuanced legal terms from the Companies Act 2013 during translation could lead to non-compliance or liability.\n  - Technical Complexity: Standardizing corporate governance jargon across regional dialects while maintaining professional gravitas is difficult.\n  - Trust and Security: Users may perceive local language tools as less secure or \"less professional\" than English counterparts in a traditionally colonial-influenced corporate culture.3-month pilot plan  - Translate core governance checklists and regulatory alerts into Hindi and Marathi\n  - Develop a bilingual (English/Hindi) mobile interface for proxy voting and board document review\n  - Conduct pilot sessions with 10 company secretaries to validate the accuracy of localized legal terminology\n  - Integrate a Hinglish-supported AI assistant for quick queries on SEBI (LODR) compliance requirements",
