        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for broad accessibility among retail shareholders and company secretaries in the North and Central Indian corporate hubs.\n  - Marathi: Critical for the high concentration of listed companies and financial institutions headquartered in Mumbai, Maharashtra.\n  - Gujarati: Vital given the significant and active community of retail investors and business promoters based in Gujarat.Critical surfaces to localize  - UX and Navigation: Dashboard labels and menu items for voting actions to ensure clarity for diverse retail investors.\n  - Content: Explanatory notes on complex proxy resolutions and voting rationales must be provided in the local language.\n  - Onboarding: Step-by-step guides for e-voting and identity verification to reduce friction for first-time digital voters.\n  - Legal: Summaries of SEBI mandates and Companies Act requirements to ensure investors understand their rights and the implications of their votes.Biggest localization risks  - Legal Accuracy: Misinterpretation of complex regulatory terminology during translation could lead to incorrect voting advice or legal non-compliance.\n  - Trust Deficit: A lack of high-quality local language support may cause retail investors to perceive the platform as exclusionary or untrustworthy.\n  - Technical Complexity: Integrating multi-language support with secure, real-time e-voting infrastructure and identity verification can increase development time and technical debt.3-month pilot plan  - Develop a trilingual (English, Hindi, Marathi) MVP interface for the core proxy voting dashboard\n  - Create localized \"How-to-Vote\" video guides and FAQs for the most common resolution types\n  - Partner with one mid-cap NSE-listed company to test the localized platform during their Annual General Meeting\n  - Implement a localized WhatsApp chatbot to handle basic shareholder queries and voting reminders",
