        "LANGUAGE LOCALIZATION": "Recommended languages  - Hindi: Essential for broad corporate compliance and communication across the northern and central business belts.\n  - Marathi: Critical for engaging the financial and corporate headquarters based in Mumbai, India's economic capital.\n  - Tamil: Vital for serving the large manufacturing and industrial sectors concentrated in Tamil Nadu.Critical surfaces to localize  - Legal and Compliance: Statutory sections like the Board's Report and BRSR must use precise Indian regulatory terminology.\n  - UX and Navigation: Internal dashboards for data submission and approval workflows for finance teams.\n  - Support and Onboarding: Technical documentation and help guides specifically addressing Indian Companies Act 2013 requirements.Biggest localization risks  - Terminology Precision: Errors in translating complex financial or legal terms can lead to significant regulatory non-compliance and reporting errors.\n  - Professional Tone: Localized content that is too informal or poorly translated will lose credibility with C-suite executives and auditors.\n  - Layout and Formatting: Indian scripts like Devanagari often require more vertical space, which can break the strict formatting required for official PDF annual reports.3-month pilot plan  - Develop a bilingual (English and Hindi) template for the core Board's Report module under Section 134 of the Companies Act\n  - Create localized tooltips for the Business Responsibility and Sustainability Reporting interface in Marathi for Mumbai-based users\n  - Partner with five mid-cap firms to validate the accuracy of localized legal drafts against existing compliance standards\n  - Implement a verification workflow where professional translators review AI-generated localized reports before final PDF export",
